    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted as a complete and documented assessment package. Although multiple credibility factors achieve levels below the MRL-5 required levels — constituting an overall 'Not accepted' regulatory disposition — the assessment itself is accepted as a valid and complete evidence package for submission. The provenance chain from the top-level claim through validation results to foundational experimental datasets is considered sufficiently documented, including the cross-study literature synthesis that provides the Bayesian coefficient posterior for Monte Carlo UQ. The identified credibility gaps are explicitly documented and will drive future V&V activities.",
